{"lemma":"أَرُزٌّ","slug":"أَرُزٌّ","root":"ر.ز.ز","root_slug":"ر-ز-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ز-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n560","n561","n562","n563","n566","n567"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8F%D8%B2%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rice","examples":[{"text":"والوجه الآخر إن يقطع له الأرض أمشارا أمشارا ويدخل فيها الماء ويقام فيها مقدار شبرة ثم ينثر الحب عليه نثرا وإذا شربت الأرض ذلك الماء غطي الرز برقيق التراب ينثر علبه بالأيادي حتى إذا مضت ساعات وتندى التراب الذي غطي به فليقام الماء في تلك المشارات فياما دائما متّصلا","english":"And the other way [of transplanting rice] is when the earth is cut into divisions and water is introduced into it to stand a handspan high, then the seeds are strewn onto it, and when the earth is soaked by this water the rice is covered with sprinkled soil strewn onto it by the hands until some hours have passed and the soil which has been strewn on it is damp too, and the water shall stand in these beds continuously and without intermission."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to insert, to drive in"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَزَّ (razza) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inserting, driving in"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a faint sound, like that which you can hear from a distance"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nProto-Indo-Iranian *wriHǰʰíš\nProto-Iranian *wriHǰíš\nProto-Iranian *wrinǰišder.\nAncient Greek ὄρυζα (óruza)bor.\nArabic رز\nBorrowed from Aramaic אֲרוּזָא (ʔăruzzā) / ܐܘܪܘܙܐ (ʔuruzzā), ܪܘܙܐ (rūzā). Doublet of بِرِنْج (birinj).\n\nbears resemblance to Aramaic רָזָ֥א (rāzā)."},"ipa":["/ruzz/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n560","headword_ar":"اَرْزٌ","root":"Arz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urozN","text_ar":"اُرْزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pine-tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajaru AlS~anawobari","text_ar":"شَجَرُ الصَّنَوْبَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or this is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arorapN","text_ar":"اَرْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arozN","text_ar":"اَرْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the pl.: (A 'Obeyd, S:) [or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arozN","text_ar":"اَرْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a coll. gen. n., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arozapN","text_ar":"اَرْزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un.:] or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male of that kind of tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arozapN","text_ar":"اَرْزَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and the author of the Minháj adds, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which does not produce fruit; but pitch"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zifot","text_ar":"زِفْت"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is extracted from its trunks and roots, and its wood is employed as a means of light, like as candles are employed; and it grows not in the land of the Arabs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"A 'Obeyd says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arozapN","text_ar":"اَرْزَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"name of a tree well known in Syria, called with us"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanawobarN","text_ar":"صَنَوْبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"because of its fruit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"he says also, I have seen this kind of tree, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arozapN","text_ar":"اَرْزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and it is called in El-'Irák"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanawobarN","text_ar":"صَنَوْبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this last is the name of the fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroz","text_ar":"اَرْز"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroEarN","text_ar":"عَرْعَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a name given to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cypress"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"juniper-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almujo*iyapi","text_ar":"المُجْذِيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavalu AlkaAfiri mavalu AlA^arozapi","text_ar":"مَثَلُ الكَافِرِ مَثَلُ الاَرْزَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlA^aroDi Hat~aY yakuwna A=nojiEaAfuhaA bimar~apK waAHidapK","text_ar":"عَلَى الاَرْضِ حَتَّى يَكُونَ ا=نْجِعَافُهَا بِمَرَّةٍ وَاحِدَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The similitude of the unbeliever is the similitude of the pine-tree standing firmly upon the ground until it is pulled up at once"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: respecting which AA and AO say that it is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^arazap","text_ar":"الاَرَزَة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; meaning the tree called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^arozan","text_ar":"الاَرْزَن"},{"kind":"text","text":": but A 'Obeyd thinks this to be a mistake, and that it is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^arozap","text_ar":"الاَرْزَة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n561","headword_ar":"اُرْزٌ","root":"Arz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arozN","text_ar":"اَرْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aruz~N","text_ar":"اَرُزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n562","headword_ar":"اَرُزٌ","root":"Arz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aruz~N","text_ar":"اَرُزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n563","headword_ar":"اُرُزٌ","root":"Arz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aruz~N","text_ar":"اَرُزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n566","headword_ar":"اَرُزٌّ","root":"Arz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uruz~N","text_ar":"اُرُزٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urozN","text_ar":"اُرْزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uruzN","text_ar":"اُرُزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aruzN","text_ar":"اَرُزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=ruzN","text_ar":"ا=رُزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruzN","text_ar":"رُزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"runozN","text_ar":"رُنْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) the first of which is the form commonly obtaining among persons of distinction; the last but one, that commonly obtaining among the vulgar; (TA;) and the last, of the dial. of 'AbdEl-Keys; (S, TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain grain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [said in the TA to be a species of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bur~","text_ar":"بُرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is an improper explanation:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there are several kinds; Egyptian and Persian and Indian; and the best kind is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jwhrY","text_ar":"جوهرى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[perhaps a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miSorY~","text_ar":"مِصْرىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or Egyptian]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is cold and dry in the second degree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moderate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hot in the first degree; and its husk is poisonous."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Minháj, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Kr"]},{"entry_id":"n567","headword_ar":"اُرُزٌّ","root":"Arz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aruz~N","text_ar":"اَرُزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}